caption: Great for a quick bite. They have some really great lunch specials - make sure to call and ask about them before ordering!

Everyone is absolutely AMAZING just like their food! They care to know your name and swear their hearts are made of gold! Everything on their menu is to die for! I love every hot entree they create taste just like home! Thank you Kendall Kitchen for making my breakfast and lunch such a wonderful experience! I look forward to seeing you guys everyday! ☺️❤️
great food for a low price....but the service makes this place the best....

Everything I have eaten here has tasted incredible. BBQ Pizza, meatball sub, breakfast burrito, all amazing with the perfect amount of CHEESE :) The ladies at the front that take my order are always so so nice. If you want to have brunch outside, they have a few seats right out in the sun.  I contacted them about getting food for my office space and Hratch got right back to me with a reasonable quote, my food was on time to pick up, and everyone at my office was so impressed with their breakfast sandwiches and fruit cups. They even were so kind as to individually wrap everything because of our COVID food policies. This place is a hidden gem in Kendall Square.
The food was delicious. The restaurant was clean and staff was very friendly. Great experience!

Delicious takeout dinner! Definitely one of the best we've had during the pandemic. Super generous portions - highly recommend the southwest chicken quesadilla (it's HUGE) and the Kendall Square Dinner Meal (we got with Teriyaki Salmon). So glad KK is doing dinner & delivery!

As far as lunch places go, you can't do a whole lot better than here. The menu is full of delicious options. I am a big fan of the chipotle chicken sandwich, and I also like the pizza. They have daily specials that are always worth a look as well. Highly recommend ordering online
Good specials, pizza and sandwiches. Check their daily specials on their Facebook. Can get packed so getting in a little early is a good idea.

Fast fast fast. Even with a huge line. Huge selection of lunch options,  hot and cold, salads and entrees. You can always find something yum and fast.

First time at this restaurant, ordered the chicken pesto melt. They were out of ciabatta, no problem. I got it on whole wheat bread. Unfortunately, I was expecting them to heat it up using a panini press or something, not the microwave. The chicken was shredded, not exactly what you want on a sandwich like that - especially when the bread is mushy and unable to hold in its contents. Had to eat it by balling it up with both hands and selectively taking bites where I thought it wouldn't completely fall apart. Tasted like it might have been a decent sandwich if it had more structural integrity and crunch.
Really delicious vegetarian options. I like that the line moves super fast too!

Worst tuna melt ever. Way overcooked.  The bread could hardly be eaten.  This place is always packed.  Order online if you're in a hurry.
Great sandwiches and fast service. Don't be intimidated if there is a line, it always moves very quickly.

We love the Kendall Kitchen! This was our family's go to spot for breakfast/lunch while staying at a Kendall Square AirBnB. The menu is diverse, the food is amazing, the staff patient, and the prices the best around. Place is airy, open, and clean. Fantastic breakfast dishes (plate best value), and delicious sandwiches, with an amazingly fresh salad bar. Salad bar adds up quickly, be aware.
I go here for coffee almost every morning and it is always great! Also lunch is good and very fast, but I think there are better lunch places nearby if you're not in a rush.
Great variety of food, fresh menu (they change everyday), affordable prices and great service. The only disadvantage is that it closes so early (at 2pm.).
It is really nice
Decent variety of food and good prices. Saves you time from choosing where to buy lunch every day! The food is not excellent, but it worth the experience

I had a good cup of coffee and an excellent cranberry orange muffin. Very clean with friendly, efficient staff. Relaxing ambiance. I'd go back to try other offerings.

I used to love this place.  The past two time they have burnt my pizza because they left it in the oven too long warming it up. The boys do not communicate with each other.  This last time he tried to cover it up with a paper plate and hide it from me!!!  I waited over 10 minutes for a slice that was already made.  I did not have time to wait for another so I ate the burnt pizza.  I am sure they don't care at all .  I think he thought it was funny at first until he saw my reaction.  I just started going back and the same person burnt a quesadilla special and hid it in the box.  He also burnt 2 pieces of pizza for a guy just ahead of me.

Far and away the best lunch spot in the area and breakfast is probably the best non-sit down breakfast place in the area.
